frameDefinitions: An Agent becomes involved in an Issue which has negative consequences for them.
A New filler occupies a Role or serves a Function after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
An Agent changes the filler of a  Role by placing a New filler in the position after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
An Entity changes, either in its category membership, its situation, or in terms of the quality of an Attribute.
A Competition comes to an end, with a Competitor tying, winning, or losing against an Opponent (or opponents) according to their Score.
frameExamples: If you <t>replace</t> me with a robot, who's gonna make excuses to your wife for you?
As soon as Tiffany kissed the frog, Tiffany <t>turned</t> into a frog.
Unbelievable--he <t>lost</t> the gold medal by just .02 points!
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Issue</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> deals with.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who is acting to deal with the <fen>Issue</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the Agent acts intentionally.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the intentional act occurs.
The new filler of the <fen>Role</fen> that was previously occupied by the <fen>Old</fen> filler.
The category that the <fen>New</fen> and <fen>Old</fen> entities fit into as a result of the <fen>Function</fen> they serve.
The (generally desirable) state of affairs that the <fen>New</fen> and <fen>Old</fen> entities are involved in bringing about.
The entity that occupied the <fen>Role</fen> or served the <fen>Function</fen> before the <fen>New</fen> filler.
The time at which the <fen>New</fen> takes up the <fen>Role</fen> previously occupied by the <fen>Old</fen>.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs actions resulting in the <fen>New</fen> entity occupying the position.
The <fen>New</fen> entity is the person or thing that the <fen>Agent</fen> sets to fill a <fen>Role</fen>.
The entity that formerly occupied the position.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the New entity.
This role identifies where the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the <fen>New</fen> entity.
The concrete or abstract entity that undergoes a change.
The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that results from the change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> belongs to before it undergoes the change.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> undergoes the transformation.
The location that the change takes place.
The individual involved in the <fen>Competition</fen>.
The individual that the <fen>Competitor</fen> has been competing against.
The individuals who compete against each other.
The event in which the <fen>Competitors</fen> compete with each other.
The time at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
The location at which the <fen>Competition</fen> takes place.
listRoleExamples: The traditional thatched roof has often been replaced <fex>by corrugated galvanized iron</fex>.
What gas replaced Hydrogen <fex>as a safer medium for use in balloons</fex> on account it does not burn?
Oil and gas replaced coal <fex>in heating homes, in industry, and in transportation</fex>.
The electron was discovered and <fex>electricity</fex> replaced gas lamps.
When electricity replaced oil <fex>in the early 1930's</fex>, the steady beam was replaced by a flashing light.
I don't know; perhaps you could substitute <fex>regular sugar</fex>.
If you substitute a 15' arm <fex>for the 50cm one</fex>, it works pretty well.
How pleasing to see that <fex>Martha</fex> has changed now.
The viccar changed <fex>from a professional clergyman</fex> into an anti-ecclesiastical activist.
